Mind-design goes 128byte
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
There's a first time for anything they say...
And this is our first 128byte-intro, just two of those blobs I'm in
love with... This time they lack palette :)


The code
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
The intro should run on VGA and RGB, and you better start it in TrueColor,
320*200 (320*240). Ofcoz there are no "init-restore" routines so a reset
is needed to quit. I had to "cheat" to get this, that means it might not
work on your falcon. If is refuses to start then boot without any .prgs or
.accs and try again. I've included the source for you so you finally can
find out how to code blobs ;) It shouldnt be too hard to optimize the
"blob-setup-source" so a palette can be added. Feel free to steal this code
and use it for your own demos or intros.

Standard program code, 128byte code + 32 program header makes 160bytes


